    strcpy writes beyond the allocated bounds of tempname. This causes a stack  
    buffer overflow, corrupting the stack and ultimately leading to a crash     
    (observed as a signal/sanitizer report due to return address corruption).   
    The issue is that strcpy does not perform bounds checking.                  
                                                                                
